	<TextInfo>
		<Text Type="Business Summary" lastModified="2015-03-17T00:33:20">Gulfsands Petroleum Plc is a United Kingdom-based independent oil and gas exploration and production company. The Companys focus is on the oil and gas exploration projects in Morocco and Tunisia. The principal activity of the Company is that of provision of services to its subsidiaries which are engaged in oil and gas production, exploration and development activities. The Company is also operator of two exploration licenses in Colombia and produces oil and gas from a portfolio of properties in the non-core United States assets, offshore Gulf of Mexico. All segments are involved with production and exploration of oil and gas. The Companys projects are in Syria, Morocco, Tunisia, Colombia and United States of America. Gulfsands Petroleum USA, Inc., Gulfsands Petroleum Sud America Limited, Gulfsands Petroleum Iraq Limited are few of the companys subsidiaries.</Text>
		<Text Type="Financial Summary" lastModified="2016-02-14T20:56:46">BRIEF: For the six months ended 30 June 2015, Gulfsands Petroleum plc revenues was not reported. Net loss before extraordinary items increased from $7.2M to $31.3M. Higher net loss reflects Morocco segment loss increase from $4M to $27.1M, Others segment loss increase of 39% to $3.1M. Basic Earnings per Share excluding Extraordinary Items decreased from -$0.06 to -$0.32.</Text>
	</TextInfo>
